(44, 15, 18, 23, 46, 9, 10, 'Known unto God are all his works', 'Divine Knowledge and Counsel', 'Both passages emphasize God''s comprehensive knowledge of all His works. Acts 15:18 states that God knows all His works from the beginning, while Isaiah 46:10 highlights His ability to declare the end from the beginning.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 18, 60, 1, 20, 20, 'known unto God are all his works', 'Divine Foreknowledge and Works', 'This connection highlights God''s foreknowledge of His works, as seen in both passages. Acts 15:18 emphasizes that all of God''s works are known from the beginning, while 1 Peter 1:20 speaks of Christ being foreordained before the foundation of the world.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 18, 44, 17, 26, 26, 'known unto God are all his works', 'Divine Sovereignty Over Creation', 'This connection highlights God''s control over all creation and the predetermined nature of human existence. Both passages emphasize that God knows and determines the works and times of all nations.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 18, 4, 23, 19, 19, 'known unto God are all his works', 'God''s Sovereignty and Truthfulness', 'This connection highlights God''s omniscience and faithfulness. Both passages emphasize that God knows all his works and does not lie, affirming his reliability in fulfilling his promises.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 18, 40, 13, 35, 35, 'from the beginning of the world', 'Divine Knowledge and Secrets', 'This connection highlights God''s omniscience and the revelation of hidden truths. Both passages emphasize knowledge and works from the foundation of the world.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 19, 44, 15, 28, 28, 'trouble not them, which from among the Gentiles', 'Gentile Inclusion in the Church', 'Both passages emphasize the decision to not impose burdens on Gentile believers. This connection highlights the unity of purpose in welcoming those who have turned to God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 19, 48, 1, 7, 10, 'trouble not them, which from among the Gentiles', 'Gospel Integrity and Gentile Believers', 'This connection highlights the concern for maintaining the integrity of the gospel and not troubling Gentile believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of not perverting the gospel of Christ, which aligns with the directive to not trouble those who have turned to God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 19, 52, 1, 9, 9, 'turned to God', 'Turning to God from Idols', 'This connection highlights the theme of turning to God, as seen in both passages. Acts 15:19 discusses Gentiles who have turned to God, while 1 Thessalonians 1:9 describes how the Thessalonians turned to God from idols.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 19, 23, 55, 7, 7, 'turned to God', 'Gentile Return to God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of returning to God. Acts 15:19 speaks of Gentiles turning to God, while Isaiah 55:7 invites the wicked to return to the Lord for mercy.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 19, 28, 14, 2, 2, 'turned to God', 'Turning to God', 'This connection highlights the theme of turning to God found in both passages. Acts 15:19 speaks of Gentiles who have turned to God, while Hosea 14:2 encourages turning to the Lord with words of repentance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 19, 44, 26, 20, 20, 'which from among the Gentiles are turned to God', 'Gentiles Turning to God', 'This connection highlights the theme of Gentiles turning to God in both passages. Acts 15:19 emphasizes not troubling those who have turned to God, while Acts 26:20 calls for Gentiles to repent and turn to God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 19, 48, 2, 4, 4, 'trouble not them, which from among the Gentiles', 'Gentile Freedom in Christ', 'This connection highlights the concern for Gentile believers'' freedom in Christ. Both passages emphasize the importance of not imposing burdens on those who have turned to God.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 20, 44, 15, 29, 29, NULL, 'Connection of Abstentions in Acts', 'Both passages emphasize the need to abstain from specific practices, including ''blood'' and ''fornication.'' This connection highlights the continuity of the instructions given to the early believers.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 20, 66, 2, 20, 20, NULL, 'Connection of Fornication and Idolatry', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of abstaining from fornication and idolatry. Acts 15:20 warns against these practices, while Revelation 2:20 addresses the consequences of allowing them within the church.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 20, 3, 3, 17, 17, 'from blood', 'Connection of Dietary Restrictions', 'Both passages emphasize the prohibition of blood. Acts 15:20''s instruction to abstain from blood parallels Leviticus 3:17''s command against eating blood.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 20, 66, 2, 14, 14, 'from pollutions of idols, and from fornication', 'Connection of Idolatry and Fornication', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of abstaining from idolatry and fornication. Acts 15:20 instructs believers to avoid ''pollutions of idols'' and ''fornication,'' while Revelation 2:14 addresses those who eat ''things sacrificed unto idols'' and commit ''fornication.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 20, 1, 9, 4, 4, 'from blood', 'Connection of Blood Prohibition', 'Both passages emphasize the prohibition of consuming blood. Acts 15:20 instructs abstaining from blood, while Genesis 9:4 explicitly states not to eat flesh with blood.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 20, 44, 21, 25, 25, NULL, 'Connection of Gentile Instructions', 'Both passages emphasize the need for Gentiles to abstain from specific practices, including ''things offered to idols'' and ''from blood.'' This connection highlights the continuity in the guidelines provided to Gentile believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 20, 46, 8, 4, 13, 'pollutions of idols', 'Idolatry and Conscience in Eating', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of abstaining from pollutions of idols and the impact of one''s actions on the conscience of others. Acts 15:20 warns against idol pollution, while 1 Corinthians 8:4-13 discusses the implications of eating food offered to idols and its effect on weaker believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 21, 44, 13, 15, 15, 'being read in the synagogues', 'Reading of the Law Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the reading of the law in synagogues. Acts 15:21 mentions Moses being preached in every city, while Acts 13:15 refers to the reading of the law and prophets in the synagogue.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 21, 44, 13, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Sabbath Readings', 'Both passages emphasize the reading of scriptures on the Sabbath. Acts 15:21 mentions that Moses is preached in synagogues every Sabbath, while Acts 13:27 refers to the voices of the prophets being read every Sabbath day.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 21, 47, 3, 14, 15, NULL, 'Connection Between Moses and Vail', 'Both passages emphasize the reading of Moses, highlighting a spiritual blindness associated with it. Acts notes that Moses is preached in every city, while 2 Corinthians discusses the vail that remains during the reading of the Old Testament.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 21, 16, 8, 1, 12, 'Moses of old time hath in every city', 'Reading of the Law', 'Both passages emphasize the public reading of the law of Moses, highlighting its importance in the community. Acts 15:21 notes that Moses is preached in every city, while Nehemiah 8:1-12 describes a specific instance of the law being read to the people.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 21, 42, 4, 16, 16, 'being read in the synagogues every sabbath day', 'Sabbath Reading in Synagogues', 'Both passages emphasize the practice of reading Moses in synagogues on the Sabbath. Acts 15:21 notes that Moses is preached in every city, while Luke 4:16 describes Jesus reading in the synagogue on the Sabbath.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 22, 44, 15, 27, 27, 'Judas surnamed Barsabas, and Silas', 'Connection of Sending Judas and Silas', 'This connection highlights the continuity of sending Judas and Silas as representatives. Both passages emphasize their role in conveying the same message to the church in Antioch.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
